        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 5:45PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 544 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Little River Falls, or near Little River Canyon National Preserve,
moving southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lebanon, Fort Payne, Mentone, Dog Town, Collbran, Adamsburg, Desoto
State Park, Little River Canyon NP, and Valley Head.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
northeastern Alabama.</instruction>
